{
  "answer": "Manu 2.230 declares that the *ācārya* (teacher), father, and mother together represent the three worlds, the three stages of life (*āśramas*), the three Vedas, and the three sacred fires—with the father equated to the Gṛhaptya fire, the mother to the Dakṣiṇāgni, and the *guru*/*ācārya* to the Āhavanīya fire (as specified immediately following in 2.231).[^1] Service to these three is the highest form of austerity (*tapas*), and no other religious duty should be undertaken without their permission.[^2]\n\n[^1]: Manusmṛti, [paragraph](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/02/translation/#p-8f1205).\n[^2]: Manusmṛti, [paragraph](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/02/translation/#p-3e3f4a).",
